buttons.subtitle: Origin Of Macaroni And Cheese
buttons.title: Macaroni and cheese - Wikipedia
buttons.snippet: The first modern recipe for macaroni and cheese was included in Elizabeth Raffald's 1769 book, The Experienced English Housekeeper. Raffald's recipe is for a Béchamel sauce with cheddar cheese—a Mornay sauce in French cooking—which is mixed with macaroni, sprinkled with Parmesan, and baked until bubbly and golden.
snippet_highlighted_words: Elizabeth Raffald's 1769 book, The Experienced English Housekeeper
